.TH "nfp_cpp_map_area" 9 "nfp_cpp_map_area" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfp_cpp_map_area \- Helper function to map an area
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u8 __iomem *" nfp_cpp_map_area
.BI "(struct nfp_cpp *cpp "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "u32 cpp_id "  ","
.BI "u64 addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "struct nfp_cpp_area **area "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpp" 12
NFP CPP handler
.IP "name" 12
Name for the area
.IP "cpp_id" 12
CPP ID for operation
.IP "addr" 12
CPP address
.IP "size" 12
Size of the area
.IP "area" 12
Area handle (output)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Map an area of IOMEM access.  To undo the effect of this function call
\fInfp_cpp_area_release_free\fP(*area).
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to memory mapped area or ERR_PTR
